{"abstract": "Some fund managers are skeptical about fossil fuel companies as long-term investments as nations move toward tougher rules on emissions.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2014/06/12/business/international/weighing-the-risks-of-investing-in-energy-companies.html", "snippet": "Some fund managers are skeptical about fossil fuel companies as long-term investments as nations move toward tougher rules on emissions.", "lead_paragraph": "LONDON \u2014 Norway\u2019s economy is highly dependent on oil and gas production, yet the Nordic country\u2019s largest private pension fund manager, Storebrand, worries about the risks of investing in companies that extract fossil fuels. Figuring that tighter regulations on carbon emissions will emerge in the coming years in an effort to combat climate change, Storebrand has decided not to invest in businesses that it believes will be hurt most by those new rules: coal companies and large producers of oil from tar sands.", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/06/12/business/12green-pic/12green-pic-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 377, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/06/12/business/12green-pic/12green-pic-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 377}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/06/12/business/12green-pic/12green-pic-jumbo.jpg", "height": 643, "width": 1024, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/06/12/business/12green-pic/12green-pic-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 1287, "width": 2048, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "